basic nmap scans:
Simple Scan: nmap 192.168.1.1 - Scans top 1000 ports.
Ping Scan (Host Discovery): nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24 - Lists active hosts without port scanning.
Subnet/Range Scan: nmap 192.168.1.0/24 or nmap 192.168.1.1-20.
Fast Scan: nmap -F 192.168.1.1 - Scans fewer ports for speed.
Service Version Detection: nmap -sV <ip> - Determines service/version info.
OS Detection: nmap -O <ip> - Identifies the operating system.
Comprehensive Scan: nmap -A <ip> - OS detection, version detection, script scanning, and traceroute.
nsloop <ip> -oN scan.txt    //save output 

Exclude IPs: nmap 192.168.1.0/24 --exclude 192.168.1.1.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
nmap port scanning:
Scan All 65,535 Ports: nmap -p- <target>
Scan Specific Ports: nmap -p 80,443,8080 <target>

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Common Verbose Options & Usage:
Basic Verbose: nmap -v <target> (Shows progress, host discovery, and open ports as found).
Double Verbose: nmap -vv <target> (More detailed information, including DNS and scan completion times).
Verbose + OS Detection: nmap -v -O <target> (Provides details on OS fingerprinting).
Verbose + Version Detection: nmap -v -sV <target> (Shows version detection progress). 
